What I learned today

- The terminal is how developers control their computer with text commands
- SSH uses a key pair system — private key stays on my machine, public key goes on GitHub
- Git tracks every change to code — nothing is ever truly lost
- A .gitignore file tells Git which files to ignore (like node_modules)
- npm is a package manager that comes with Node.js
- Public repositories on GitHub are visible to recruiters worldwide

*Mistakes I made today
- Typed `catm` instead of `cat` with a space — learned that spaces matter in terminal commands
- Used wrong terminal (Command Prompt) instead of Git Bash on Windows

*How I fixed them
- Read the error message carefully and spotted the typo
- Switched to Git Bash which supports Linux-style commands

